29/12/2010
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- Police arrested on Tuesday (December 28th) a former member of a Serb paramilitary group suspected of war crimes committed during the Kosovo conflict.
Milojko Nikolic, 46, was detained based on an arrest warrant issued by Belgrade.
He is suspected of taking part in the 1999 killing of 44 Albanian civilians in the Kosovo village of Cuska.
Nikolic, a member of "The Jackals" paramilitary unit, will be extradited to Serbia soon.
(RTCG, Cafe del Montenegro, AP - 28/12/10)
